article.headline: Alabama A&M 72, Jackson State 62
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Obie Trotter had 20 points and Michael Ford added 17 to lead Alabama A&M to a 72-62 win over Jackson State on Thursday night. Joe Martin added 11 points for A&M (12-12, 10-7 Southwestern Athletic Conference), which won its fourth straight game. Jackson State (14-15, 10-7) was led by Dakari Wallace's 15 points. Trey Johnson added 14 points and Charlie White had 11 for the Tigers, whose two-game winning streak was snapped. Alabama A&M led 41-32 at halftime and held Jackson State to 36 percent shooting.
